[h1]Exceptions[/h1]

Different exceptions are raised for different reasons. 
Common exceptions:
[b]ImportError[/b]: an import fails;
[b]IndexError[/b]: a list is indexed with an out-of-range number;
[b]NameError[/b]: an unknown variable is used;
[b]SyntaxError[/b]: the code can't be parsed properly; 
[b]TypeError[/b]: a function is called on a value of an inappropriate type;
[b]ValueError[/b]: a function is called on a value of the correct type, but with an inappropriate value.
[note]Python has several other built-in exceptions, such as ZeroDivisionError and OSError. Third-party libraries also often define their own exceptions.[/note]
